<br>
Wizard Resist spells and Shieldings (Ac, Hp, MR).<br>
<br>
Currently, Shaman focus overwrites our Shieldings, CoS overwrites our FR/CR resists, and Talismans overwrite the new PR/DR buffs. All of these buffs are SELF ONLY. I would like to see these buffs be able to stack with all other buffs. They would give wizards an edge, but being self only, I don't think would be overpowering or unbalancing in any fashion. As well, the total buff / debuff limit (15, right?) would prevent wizards from keeping them all up, we would have to be choosy about which ones we employed anyways.<br>
<br>
In the current raid situation, I see no reason for so many of our self only buff lines to be so completly useless, but I would love to be able to actually use these new spells I'm reciving.<br>
<br>
This thoughts were inspired when I recived the new elemental self only shielding, PR and DR, which was promptly overwritten no more than two minuets after I recived it in an exp group by a shaman. Looking towards my recently garnered FR/CR upgrade, and the shielding upgrades, I'm frustrated.<br>
<br>
<br>
I belive that their usefulness and value would increase dramatically if they were stackable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=samadhibots>Samadhi BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Batshit Insane<BR>Warren Sapp's bitch<BR><a href=mailto:samadhi@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Samadhi</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 4134<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/25/02 2:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Self Only Buff Stacking?</span><hr size=1> oh hawx your so hot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 6378<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/25/02 4:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Self Only Buff Stacking?</span><hr size=1> I think the idea behind the self buffs for Wizards is for solo work, they don't stack with much (in fact, they stack with even fewer things than they used to).  It allows the Wizard to function more safely alone I think is the logic, but who can say.  SOE is rightly concerned about being able to stack so much cool stuff on people they become nearly unbeatable (for instance, if you could stack every single HP buff at once on a tank they'd have monster-level hps, if you could stack every single resistance buff at once on yourself you'd have 255 in all resistances and laugh at attacks).  But there's probably room for argument that it could be relaxed a little, at least. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midgetgod>Midget God</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/25/02 7:06 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Self Only Buff Stacking?</span><hr size=1> I think making them stack would be bad. It will only trivial content. I don't cheat my way through the game b/c its not fun to me. Now, I do think it'd be cool and all if they stacked but in reality I would not enjoy the game as much. Our buffs have <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>always</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> not been the best. Almost all our buffs can be overwritten by true buff classes.<br>
<br>
Our Elemental Cloak is the EXACT same thing as Circle of Seaons but its self only. I think that is great. I used to solo in OS a whole lot and if you've ever done it alot you'd realise the importance of resists. Now, I don't have to rely on any other class to get the same resist buffs pre-PoP when I'm soloing.<br>
<br>
On a side note, the Wizard Epic and Spiritual Purity is a complete other issue and IMO they should stack b/c they are completely different buffs. <p>[60 Sorcerer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> (Gnome) <<a href="http://www.insublimity.com">Sublimity</a>></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zuminozufeilon>Zumino Zufeilon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/30/02 9:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard Self Only Buff Stacking?</span><hr size=1> I actually think they should be able to stack.  Simply put, these are self only, making the tissuepaper class a bit more resistant to the AE's that are popular on mobs wouldn't be unbalancing.  All it would do would lessen our drain on healers mana.<br>
<br>
Heck, as it is, to have a decent chance of resisting most stuff you need 250+ resists, and I can get there easily with bard buffs(heck, I can almost get there without bardbuffs), but what's another 30ish points on the stacking things, especially as they can't be cast on other things.<br>
<br>
The non-stacking of Okiel's Lev and elemental armor/cloak is just dumb in my book though. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15672"> Mistress Zumino Zufeilon </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28261"> Cedori the Drunken Monkie </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kswilson>kswilson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/5/02 7:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Levity</span><hr size=1> Two things about this spell and stacking that I find annoying.  First, not stacking with my own personal resist buff is stupid, and second, the fact that any damage shield of any class will over right it and make me fall.  Its pretty irritating to have to unclick a druid group ds and recast my lev spell.  And it has to potential to kill me if a nasty druid decided that I should fall from great heights for some reason.<br>
